title: 🦧  "To avoid criticism, do nothing, say nothing, be nothing." - Elbert Hubbard
content:
Given a basic Lisp-like string expression, parse it (where the available functions are add, subtract, multiply, and divide, and they all take in 2 values). Examples:

$ babyLisp('(add 1 2)') $ 3 $ babyLisp('(multiply 4 (add 2 3))') $ 20
